description: An intelligent code review system that uses machine learning to automatically detect bugs, suggest improvements, and ensure code quality. The system analyzes code patterns, identifies potential security vulnerabilities, and provides detailed feedback to developers. It integrates with popular development environments and supports multiple programming languages including Python, JavaScript, Java, and C++.
team_members: Alice Johnson, Bob Smith, Carol Davis

description: A mobile app that helps students navigate university campuses using AR technology with real-time directions and accessibility support. The app uses computer vision to recognize campus landmarks and provides turn-by-turn navigation with voice guidance. It includes features for wheelchair accessibility, visual impairment support, and real-time updates about campus events and closures.
tech_stack: React Native, ARCore, Firebase, Google Maps API

description: A comprehensive platform for tracking and reducing carbon footprints with personalized recommendations and community challenges. Users can log their daily activities, transportation choices, and consumption habits. The app provides detailed analytics, sets achievable goals, and connects users with local environmental initiatives. It includes gamification elements to encourage sustainable behavior.
team_members: Frank Miller, Grace Lee, Henry Taylor, Ivy Chen
tech_stack: Vue.js, Node.js, MongoDB, Chart.js, Stripe API

description: A secure, transparent voting system built on blockchain technology ensuring voter anonymity while providing verifiable results. The system uses smart contracts to manage the voting process and cryptographic proofs to ensure vote integrity. It supports multiple voting methods including ranked choice and approval voting.
team_members: Liam O'Connor, Maya Patel, Noah Kim

description: A comprehensive telemedicine platform that connects patients with healthcare providers through secure video consultations. The platform includes features for appointment scheduling, prescription management, medical record sharing, and real-time health monitoring. It supports multiple languages and includes accessibility features for patients with disabilities.
team_members: Sarah Ahmed, Michael Chen, Priya Sharma, Alex Rodriguez
tech_stack: React, Node.js, WebRTC, PostgreSQL, AWS, Twilio

description: An AI-powered tutoring system that provides personalized learning experiences for students. The system adapts to individual learning styles and paces, providing customized content and practice problems. It includes natural language processing for answering student questions and computer vision for analyzing handwritten work.
tech_stack: Python, OpenAI API, Flask, TensorFlow, OpenCV

description: A mobile application that helps restaurants and households track and reduce food waste. Users can log food items, track expiration dates, and receive suggestions for recipes using ingredients that are about to expire. The app connects with local food banks to facilitate donations of excess food.
team_members: Maria Garcia, Tom Wilson, Lisa Park
tech_stack: Flutter, Firebase, Google Vision API, Maps API

description: A virtual reality fitness application that provides immersive workout experiences. Users can choose from various environments and workout routines, with real-time form correction and progress tracking. The app includes multiplayer features for group workouts and social challenges.
team_members: Kevin Zhang, Rachel Green, Marcus Johnson, Sofia Martinez
tech_stack: Unity, C#, Oculus SDK, Blender, Firebase
